'''Fathammer''' was a [[video game]] publisher and [[video game developer|developer]] based in [[Finland]]. They have developed game [[cell phones]], the [[Tapwave Zodiac]], and also the [[Gizmondo]].{{Citation needed|date=March 2009}} Fathammer was acquired by Telcogames in June 2006, and X-Forge game development environment developed by Fathammer was sold to [[Acrodea]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Telcogames buys Fathammer, sells X-Forge|url = http://www.fiercemobilecontent.com/story/telcogames-buys-fathammer-sells-x-forge/2006-06-06|accessdate = 12 May 2011}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title = Fathammer kutistui brittiomistukseen|url = http://www.tietoviikko.fi/taustat/kaikki_jutut/article137243.ece|language = Finnish|accessdate = 12 May 2011}}</ref>

