''[[Bigg Boss (Hindi TV series)|Bigg Boss]]'' is a television reality show broadcast on [[Viacom 18|Colors channel]] and star vijay channel in India. It follows the ''[[Big Brother (franchise)|Big Brother]]'' format, which was first developed by [[Endemol]] in the Netherlands. Within a span of 11 years of telecast, ''Bigg Boss'' has rolled out 11 seasons (season 11, last aired on Colors) and one spin-off version thus establishing itself as one of the most popular reality TV series in India.
==Season 2== {{Main|Bigg Boss (Hindi season 2)}}
* [[Rahul Mahajan]] made headlines when he broke the rules of the show and escaped over the house by jumping over the wall.<ref name='pinkvilla1/> * [[Raja Chaudhary]] and [[Sambhavna Seth]] abused each other before getting really intimate. They were also caught kissing during the show.<ref name="topyaps1">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/5-times-bride-to-be-Sambhavna-Seth-courted-controversy/articleshow/53155056.cms|title=5 times bride-to-be Sambhavna Seth courted controversy|last=|first=|date=|website=[[The Times of India]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
==Season 3== {{Main|Bigg Boss (Hindi season 3)}}
* In the third season, housemate [[Vindu Dara Singh]] was often credited as [[Akshay Kumar]]'s favourite housemate after playing Kumar’s sidekick in “[[Kambakkht Ishq]]”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.masala.com/15624-akshay-plays-godfather-to-vindu-dara-singh |title=Akshay plays godfather to Vindu Dara Singh |publisher=Masala.com |date= |accessdate=2012-01-13}}</ref> and becoming good friends with him. With being hated by fellow inmates inside the house for his conduct accompanied by the resentment against him from the audiences [[Vindu Dara Singh|Vindu]] survived seven evictions after consecutively getting nominated from eighth week onwards. Vindu went on to win the season and was also announced the most stylish and bold contestant consequently winning a [[Chevrolet Cruze]] and Rs. 1 [[crore]].
* Contestant [[Kamal Rashid Khan]] had caused ruckus inside the house which lead to a controversial exit by makers after he threw a bottle and [[Rohit Verma]] but later hit [[Shilpa Shetty]]'s sister, [[Shamita Shetty]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Bigg-Boss-expels-Kamaal-Khan/articleshow/5147730.cms|title=Bigg Boss expels Kamaal R Khan|date=22 October 2009}}</ref>
==Season 4== {{Main|Bigg Boss (Hindi season 4)}}
* TV actors [[Sara Khan (TV actress)|Sara Khan]] and [[Ali Merchant]] were paid Rs.50 lakh to get married on the show.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sara Khan and Ali Merchant to get paid to marry on 'Bigg Boss' | url=http://m.indiatoday.in/story/sara-khan-and-ali-merchant-to-get-paid-to-marry-on-bigg-boss/1/119422.html|publisher=[[India Today]] }}</ref> The wedding is considered forbidden in [[Islam]], because Sara Khan and Ali Merchant were already married.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/sara-ali-wedding-against-islam/story-ULOIHfHmJuzQcboAR62gHP.html|title=Sara-Ali wedding against Islam|publisher =[[Hindustan Times]] }}</ref> Ali Merchant's mother, Salma, however, said Muslim law permitted the same couple to remarry as many times as they wished to.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/mumbai/other//amp_articleshow/16072625.cms|title= BIGG MISTAKE, SAY MUSLIM LEADERS|publisher =[[Mumbai Mirror]] }}</ref> * [[Pakistan]]i actress [[Veena Malik]] was involved in physical relationship with [[Ashmit Patel]].<ref name='pinkvilla1'>{{cite web|title= Bigg Boss 11: From KRK to Swami Om, meet Bigg Boss' most controversial contestants ever| url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/tv/news-gossip/bigg-boss-11-krk-swami-om-meet-bigg-boss-most-controversial-contestants-ever-387178?amp|publisher =PinkVilla.com}}</ref> * During the [[Bigg Boss (Season 4)|fourth season]], TV actress Sara Khan objected to the Bigg Boss' behaviour towards fellow-housemate [[Dolly Bindra]]. Ever since [[Dolly Bindra]] re-entered the house, there had been quite a bit of a change in her stance and attitude towards the inmates of the house. Dolly became quite polite and got some benefits like she was made the queen immediately after she re-entered, thereby enabling her to get certain benefits that the others couldn't even dream of. Thus, with almost everyone quite flabbergasted, Sara protested against partiality towards Dolly. Sara kept on complaining that 'Bigg Boss' was not fair at which [[Samir Soni]], who too, had re-entered agreed with what Sara had to say. [[Sara Khan (TV actress)|Sara]] was later strictly warned by the Bigg Boss and host [[Salman Khan]] regarding these vague accusations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://frontierindia.net/big-boss-4-sara-khan-accuses-big-boss-of-being-partial-to-dolly-bindra |title=Big Boss 4 : Sara Khan accuses Big Boss of being partial to Dolly Bindra |publisher=Frontier India |date=2010-12-09 |accessdate=2012-01-13}}</ref>
==Season 5== {{Main|Bigg Boss (Hindi season 5)}}
* Pooja Missra who was constantly bullied on the show was ejected. She gave her fellow contestant Siddarth Bhardwaj a little push, which the makers decided to evict her. However, the TRP became really low, as the show started losing its viewership. The TRP even came at 0.69 at one point. <ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tv/Bigg-Boss-5-Pooja-Missra-thrown-out/opinions/10880054.cms</ref>
==Season 6== {{Main|Bigg Boss (Hindi season 6)}}
* Soon after the entry of Kashif Qureshi, a common man chosen via auditions held across India, as an inmate of the house the whole exercise of selecting an unknown person to be part of ''Bigg Boss'' seemed to have come into question and has been reportedly a planned one. After Kashif was selected from the three short-listed hopefuls to enter the house the media scrutinized every detail that linked to Kashif's background. Unexpectedly Qureshi was found to personally know [[Salman Khan]] since he was shooting ''[[Wanted (2009 film)|Wanted]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/idiotbox/bigg-boss-6-common-man-kashif-qureshi-s-entry-courtesy-salman-khan_120823.htm|title=Bigg Boss 6: Common man Kashif Qureshi's entry courtesy Salman Khan?|work=[[Zee News]] |accessdate=18 December 2015}}</ref> * Contestant Iman Siddiqui made a statement about host Salman Khan that Salman Khan owed him money.<ref>{{cite web|title=Imam Siddique slams Salman Khan|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/tabloid/imam-siddique-slams-salman-khan/story-OC9ZTVPoImgQdODYMsh1KP.html|publisher=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate=8 December 2017}}</ref> He also removed his clothes after a midnight fight with his co-participant.
==Season 7== {{Main|Bigg Boss (Hindi season 7)}}
* [[Armaan Kohli]] was arrested from the set of the show when a complaint filed by British singer-actress [[Sofia Hayat]] for allegedly assaulting her during their stay in the show.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-bigg-boss-7-actor-armaan-kohli-arrested-for-assaulting-fellow-inmate-sofia-hayat-twitteratti-hail-action-1936386|title=Bigg Boss 7: Actor Armaan Kohli arrested for 'assaulting' fellow inmate Sofia Hayat; Twitteratti hail action |publisher =[[DNA India]] }}</ref> * The host Salman Khan was caught favoring [[Tanisha Mukherjee]] instead of [[Kushal Tandon]] despite her unarguably violent behavior and Khan supported all of Mukherjee’s wrongdoings.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/salman-khan-explains-his-outburst-at-kushal-on-bigg-boss-7/|title=Salman Khan explains his outburst at Kushal on Bigg Boss 7|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Indian Express]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
==Season 8== {{Main|Bigg Boss (Hindi season 8)}}
* [[Karishma Tanna]] had a big fight with [[Gautam Gulati]] after he abused her during the Hijack task in the second week after Sonali's eviction. This lead to whole house turning against Gautam.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/ugly-fight-between-karishma-tanna-gautam-gulati-bigg-boss-8-has-finally-arrived/|title=‘Bigg Boss 8’ witnesses first ugly fight between Karishma Tanna, Gautam Gulati|date=30 September 2014}}</ref>
* The introduction of special panel members on occasional eviction episodes came under controversy during the season. The production team was mainly accused for violating the concept of the original ''[[Big Brother (TV series)|Big Brother]]'' franchise and allowing interference from external agents into the house environment. The second week saw appearances from [[VJ Andy|Andy]] and [[Kamya Punjabi|Kamya]] who were seen forcing their opinions on the housemates by calling it a guide to their stay. However Kamya, on a relative off-note, went on to malign targeted housemates' stance and reputation by wording her take as the 'viewer's point of view'.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pinkvilla.com/tvtags/salman-khan/bigg-boss-8-dapper-salman-diwali-mood-grills-contestants-not-supporting-sonali|title=Bigg Boss 8: Dapper Salman in diwali mood grills contestants for not supporting Sonali!|publisher=Pinkvilla.com|accessdate=16 November 2014}}</ref> Subsequent to the episode's airing critics termed her conduct as 'adding script to a rather spontaneous programme'. A similar incident took place in the fourth week where [[Sargun Mehta]]'s argument with Minissha received much backlash from viewers.<ref name="bollywoodlife.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/bigg-boss-8-gauhar-khan-gets-into-a-war-of-words-with-minissha-lamba/|title=Bigg Boss 8: Gauhar Khan gets into a war of words with Minissha Lamba! – Bollywood News & Gossip, Movie Reviews, Trailers & Videos at Bollywoodlife.com|publisher=[[BollywoodLife.com]] |accessdate=16 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.glamcapture.com/gauahar-khan-and-sargun-mehta-make-an-appearance-in-big-boss-8/|title=Gauahar Khan and Sargun Mehta make an appearance in Big Boss 8 Weekend Ka Vaar|work=GlamCapture.Com|accessdate=16 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ignarchives.com/gauhar-khan-and-sargun-mehta-as-special-guests-on-bigg-boss-8-weekend-ka-vaar-episode/|title=Gauhar Khan and Sargun Mehta as special guests on Bigg Boss 8 Weekend Ka Vaar Episode!|author=Sidharth Banerjee|work=Bollywood IGN|accessdate=16 November 2014}}</ref> Despite demands and complaints from viewers, the broadcaster declined the opportunity to explain the addition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://colors.in.com/in/biggboss/videos/gauahar-comes-to-weekend-ka-vaar-with-salman-bb8-10101228-3.html|title=Bigg Boss season 8 Videos -Gauahar comes to Weekend ka Vaar with Salman, Bigg Boss 8 Reality TV Show Videos, Clips |work=Colors.in.com|accessdate=16 November 2014}}</ref> Furthermore, [[Salman Khan]] was also criticized for siding with [[Sonali Raut]] without a hint of care for housemates' or viewers' opinion and judgement citing the live feed as enough proof for evaluation. However viewers expressed disapprobation since the live feed being released on the channel's website was only broadcasting previously recorded content.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/bollywood/bigg-boss-8-salman-khan-grills-karishma-tanna-diandra-17806.html|title=Bigg Boss 8: Salman Khan again grills Karishma Tanna, declares Gauahar Khan to be the Bigg Boss (view pics)|publisher=[[India TV]] |accessdate=16 November 2014}}</ref> * In November 2014, on [[Gautam Gulati]]'s birthday, [[Diandra Soares]] had took him into the bathroom which lead to another controversial topic of the house.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/bigg-boss-8-gautam-gulati-diandra-soares-bathroom-scene-shocks-viewers-615399|title=Bigg Boss 8: Gautam Gulati, Diandra Soares Flirt in Bathroom: Viewers Blast them|date=27 November 2014}}</ref> After Diandra's eviction, there was another controversial topic after reports started saying she was pregnant when she reportedly went to the hospital but later she denied all of the rumours.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.india.com/showbiz/shocking-bigg-boss-8-is-diandra-soares-pregnant-with-gautam-gulatis-child-220846/|title=Shocking! Bigg Boss 8: Is Diandra Soares pregnant with Gautam Gulati’s child?|date=13 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/kissing-doesnt-lead-pregnancy-pregnant-diandra-soares-1850035.html|title=Kissing doesn't lead to pregnancy, I am not pregnant: Diandra Soares|date=14 December 2014}}</ref> * [[Ali Quli Mirza]] was trying to escape from the show by climbing up the rooftop to escape the house where he was slapped by [[Sonali Raut]] for passing inappropriate remarks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/bigg-boss-celebs-who-were-thrown-out-of-the-house/photostory/45041875.cms|title=Bigg Boss: Celebs who were thrown out of the house|accessdate=9 December 2017|publisher=[[The Times of India]]}}</ref>
===Halla Bol=== {{Main|Bigg Boss Halla Bol}}
* This series was marked by a number of downfalls for the ''Big Brother'' franchise in India. The continuation of the regular celebrity season into an All-Stars version garnered initial media and viewer attention but the ratings for the show decreased to an all-time low with the final only managing to score a [[Target rating point|TRP]] of 2.82.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-trp-report-bigg-boss-8-does-not-live-up-to-the-mark-2025485|title=TRP Report: 'Bigg Boss 8' does not live up to the mark - Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis|date=13 October 2014|publisher=[[DNA India]]}}</ref> The official tabulators for the show being [[Ernst & Young]] allegedly had formed the final result based on a number of votes which was more than any of the previous seasons.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/satyamev-jayate-3-has-better-trp-ratings-bigg-boss-8-aamir-khan-beats-salman-613913|title='Satyamev Jayate 3' has Better TRP Ratings than 'Bigg Boss 8': Aamir Khan Beats Salman|first=Shekhar H|last=Hooli|publisher=[[IBTimes]] }}</ref> An additional statement released by the firm revealed that the percentage separating the final two contenders was extravagantly huge, with [[Gautam Gulati]] winning by an unprecedented margin, that was larger than ever before.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-bigg-boss-halla-bol-gautam-gulati-is-the-winner-2057107|title=Bigg Boss Halla Bol: Gautam Gulati crowned the winner - Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis|date=31 January 2015|publisher=[[DNA India]] }}</ref>
