==Season 10== {{Main|Bigg Boss (Hindi season 10)}}
* Priyanka Jagga, after creating fights in the house and saying nasty things to [[Lopamudra Raut]] and [[Antara Biswas|Monalisa]] had got kicked out by host [[Salman Khan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/bigg-boss-10-salman-khan-throws-priyanka-jagga-out-of-the-house/articleshow/56150804.cms|title=Bigg Boss 10: Salman Khan throws Priyanka Jagga out of the house|date=24 December 2016}}</ref>
* Contestant Swami Om put his urine on co-contestants Bani and Rohan. Later, the makers of the show evicted Swami Om. He has had several exits before on the show but later came back.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bigg-boss-season-10/bigg-boss-10-swami-om-pees-bani-and-rohan-bigg-boss-evicts-him-4459807/lite/|title=Bigg Boss 10: Swami Om pees on Bani and Rohan, Bigg Boss evicts him|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Indian Express]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref>
*The fight between [[Gurbani Judge|Bani J]] and [[Lopamudra Raut]] got ugly after the BB Call Centre" which lead to Bani trying to strangle Lopamudra's neck.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bigg-boss-season-10/bigg-boss-10-enemies-bani-j-lopamudra-raut-get-into-scuffle-4471124/|title=Bigg Boss 10: Enemies Bani J, Lopamudra Raut get into scuffle|date=13 January 2017}}</ref>
* The voting rules for the final week were changed abruptly following [[Rohan Mehra]]'s eviction. The previous rule which allowed multiple votes, capped at 99, per IP and phone number were brought down to 1. This created uproar from the viewers who were not officially or appropriately informed of the tweak. The voters were not refunded money for any additional votes they had made since 1 vote submission from online and offline sources was recorded and the rest were discarded. [[Viacom 18]] received 570 complaints during the night of the final when Manu Punjabi was shown to have quit the competition before the results were announced. Realising that the final was pre-recorded with the outcome known to the producers before the episode aired the viewers were appalled that voting lines for Manu were kept open throughout. The complaints increased overnight to a record 1140 after the final had finished airing. Manveer Gurjar, a commoner who ended up winning the season, received one of the highest number of votes in the history of the show. {{citation needed|date=October 2017}}
